org.batfish.z3

Class BDDIpAccessListSpecializer

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.batfish.z3.IpAccessListSpecializer
      • org.batfish.z3.BDDIpAccessListSpecializer
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    GenericAclLineMatchExprVisitor<AclLineMatchExpr>

    public final class BDDIpAccessListSpecializer
extends IpAccessListSpecializer
    An IpAccessListSpecializer that uses BDDs to represent the headerspace of interest. The intuition of specialization is to remove parts of the ACL that are irrelevant for the headerspace of interest.

    The superclass IpAccessListSpecializer walks over the ACL and its match expressions, downcalling at the match expression leaves. For each leaf, we compute the space matched by that expression (as a BDD) and compare with the space of interest. There are three cases:

    1. The two spaces are disjoint. Then the expression is not relevant to the space of interest, and will be replaced by the FalseExpr.INSTANCE.
    2. The match expression space contains the space of interest. Then the expression is relevant, but we also know that it will always evaluate to true. We can optionally optimize such expressions by replacing them with TrueExpr.INSTANCE.
    3. The match expression intersects, but does not contain the space of interest. We preserve the expression as-is.
